Let us consider the problem posed by the blind recognition of seven STBCs included in the IEEE 802.16e standard [35]:

•
a \$1/2\$-rate orthogonal code: OSTBC\$(4,4,8)\$;
•
a \$3/4\$-rate orthogonal code: OSTBC\$(4,3,4)\$;
•
a 1-rate code: STBC\$(4,4,4)\$;
•
two 2-rate codes: STBC\$(4,8,4)\$ and STBC\$(4,4,2)\$;
•
a 3-rate code: STBC\$(4,6,2)\$;
•
a 4-rate code: STBC\$(4,4,1)\$ (spatial multiplexing).

 [10]]:

